<paragraph id="8BDE5D103144FFA1FF2EFA93FDFAF9A4" blockId="9.[151,1436,885,1591]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="B91581023144FFA1FF2EFA93FEF1FA3C" bold="true" box="[198,320,1405,1431]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C6126933144FFA1FDB5FA93FC02FA3C" authority="Dai and Zhang" authorityName="Dai and Zhang" box="[605,947,1405,1431]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Abrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coneus">
<emphasis id="B91581023144FFA1FDB5FA93FD4CFA3D" box="[605,765,1405,1430]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Abrus coneus</emphasis>
Dai and Zhang
</taxonomicName>
externally, but can be distinguished from the latter by: 
<number id="3DA94F373144FFA1FED8FA4BFE8CFA14" box="[304,317,1445,1471]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" value="1.0">1</number>
) pygophore without long appendage at ventral posterior margin; 
<number id="3DA94F373144FFA1FBDEFA4BFBF4FA14" box="[1078,1093,1445,1471]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" value="2.0">2</number>
) aedeagal shaft about as long as basal projection, with ventral triangular flange subapically; 
<number id="3DA94F373144FFA1FC60FA23FC26FA4C" box="[904,919,1485,1511]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" value="3.0">3</number>
) aedeagal projection tapered to acute apex and deeply concave at dorsal margin.
</paragraph>
